 the people who have light and dark on the same team.<br>
<br>
I can handle the allied lights, but sometimes that just comes to bite you.  Id prefer a server where they didnt exploit the crossteaming crap.<br>
<br>
I hear there are high level &quot;prophet&quot; type guilds that have all 4 teams.<br>
<br>
is RZ the place to be.. or are Vallon Tallon better? or worse.<br>
<br>
Hats off to the Shanks and other 1 (non-dark) team guilds... playing it the way it was meant to be played.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usgean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sgean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/01 12:23:48 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/voxton/sgean/sgean-photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VZ and TZ</span><hr size=1> There are still problems with this, yes.  <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/voxton/sgean/homey.jpg><BR>
Homey 't Knife<BR>
Shank, and Thug of Vallon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usterk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sterk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/16/01 8:01:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> OBR</span><hr size=1> Yeah, them damn OBR guys are cross-teamer scum!<br>
<br>
-Sterk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/16/01 11:51:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OBR</span><hr size=1> Then you have those damn &quot;Cross-Class&quot; guilds.<br>
<br>
KOS! <p><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</b><BR>
Crime Boss of Vallon Zek<BR>
{Order of the Black Rose}<BR>
---------------------------<BR><i>
"No man can separate what we create...<BR> OBR at its finest, thugs for life, assassins for hire.  Can ya feel me?  Well feel this..."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urivenwry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rivenwry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/01 7:21:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OBR</span><hr size=1> *laugh*<br>
<br>
I don't know about things on other servers (tallon, hehe) but on Vallon, there's are basically three powerful factions:<br>
<br>
Defiant : All lights<br>
<br>
Xanit K'ven : All darkies <br>
<br>
And the PMS gang (hahaha) : Prophets, Silent Souls, and   Malevolance<br>
<br>
Defiant and Xanit are basically even in power.  The PMS gang hit a snag when they terrorized the server for months and then promptly had every single person besides themselves make it their personal mission to make the PMS gang's live's miserable.  They're a little nerfed lately.  <br>
<br>
Anyhow, to make it plainly clear: 3 teams together are roughly equal to the power of the darks ONE team.  So...<br>
<br>
If everybody was to play all the teams vs. each other, every single pvp encounter (more than a girly skirmish) will involve the darkies kicking everybody else's ass.  I don't know about dumb people, but SMART people would team up.  This is a ROLEPLAYING game, where people adjust and acclamate to the environment.  Come to Vallon and kill everybody who's not on your team---pretty soon you'll get to have people who check the world for your name (like a certain Aababa) every 15 minutes and, once you ARE online, spread it to their entire guild, which spreads to other guilds, which lets you spend an honest half an hour an online experience, after which you will get your ass kicked by everybody and all of everybodies friends.  Just ask Prophets.  <br>
<br>
Don't think I write in anger or annoyance---I'm a cool headed rogue.  But let me tell you, the Kill-all-who-you-can-touch thing disappears after you're level 30 or so, and the few who DO do it, well...they tend to disappear after a few weeks of unending beatings.<br>
<br>
Rivenwry <p>I know what you're doing...
I see it all, too clear.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/teenyknot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/01 8:08:18 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/fricka_on_vallon_zek/FrickaNEWlt.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OBR</span><hr size=1> ::chuckles::<br>
<br>
Of yes, the pure team players...they never last a month.<br>
<br>
Of course someone said that to my guild over a year ago.<br>
<br>
ROLEPLAYING as the previous poster shouted, surely does come in all forms... perhaps even singlemindedness forms. Aabbaba is long gone. He wasn't roleplaying, he was a grief player and he got the treatment you described because of it.<br>
<br>
One can roleplay one team against all the rest without being a grief player. That's how you do it.  The times have been changing, and others have followed our pure team, roleplaying lead. The Dal Kingdom (Formerly of Royal House Thex but split off because they wish to have RHT be all &quot;evil&quot; so as not to cause confusion) is now making a move to support pure team play.  They are elven, the team that everyone says could never do it.  <br>
<br>
You are a rogue, perhaps one that remembers back when others despaired because playing a rogue was &quot;too hard&quot; &quot;dumb&quot; &quot;you'll never get to the plains/a decent level/get a group/etc&quot;.<br>
<br>
If you chose a rogue despite all of that, perhaps you might just understand why people have chosen to play single team and not imply that just because they chose to go against the grain that they are not &quot;SMART&quot;.<br>
<br>
One can simply adapt to a PvP environment, or one can influence its growth.  The pure team players have chosen to make their mark on Vallon Zek's history. <p><table border=0 align=left width=100%>
