<br>
For us, the times that have been changing have been from one 4team uber jackass guild loosing power to a 3 team guild.  <br>
<br>
Xanit holds its own as a 1 team guild.  So it's possible to do it.  Of course keeping in mind the ratio of high level darkies to high level shorties/elves/humans, it's not so surprising.<br>
<br>
Rivenwry <p>I know what you're doing...
I see it all, too clear.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gaintook>Gain Took</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/01 10:09:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VZ and TZ</span><hr size=1> Tallon is also plagued by &quot;crossteaming guilds&quot;. However this is only the case post-50. Otherwise it remains mainly light versus dark or even one team, (though that's not very common). The problem is that there aren't enough strong guilds to dominate anywhere. As a result, these cross-teamers don't have that much of an effect, except of course when it comes to planes/uber mobs, in which case if you don't crossteam (4 teams) then you cant even attempt trak or VS. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufscsaber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FSC Saber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/01 1:13:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VZ and TZ</span><hr size=1> Um there is only one Xteam guild on Tallon at 50+ and they mostly stick all together for whatever they are doing and are not as much a problem as everybody makes it sound. Im not sure where your ideas about TZ are but they are pretty wrong about hi levels.<br>
<br>
Rainne<br>
53rd Rogue<br>
Tallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gaintook>Gain Took</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/24/01 12:22:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VZ and TZ</span><hr size=1> It's only a trend. It's far from horrible, but still, the trend towards more and more blue. I think of all the servers i've played on, Tallon is the most unblue of all of them, but who knows with Panda's in the future.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/24/01 4:26:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VZ and TZ</span><hr size=1> Now I have a reason to level past thirty.  Oughtta be fun to get so much attention from layin out elves and halflings. <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>

